OL,6,FThe doctor admitted to taking
OL,7,Fadvantage of Perry, knowing he was a
OL,8,Fstruggling addict. Plasencia texted
OL,9,Fanother doctor that Perry was a
OL,10,F"moron" who could be exploited for
OL,11,Fmoney, according to court filings.
OL,13,FProsecutors had asked for three years
OL,14,Fin prison, while the defence sought
OL,15,Fjust a day in prison, plus probation.
OL,17,FPlasencia was led from the courtroom
OL,18,Fin handcuffs as his mother cried
OL,19,Floudly in the audience.
